import { Badge, AppBar, Grid, IconButton, Toolbar, Button, Avatar } from '@material-ui/core'
import React from 'react'
import NotificationsIcon from '@material-ui/icons/Notifications';
import PersonIcon from '@material-ui/icons/Person';

export default function Header() {
    return (
        <AppBar position='static' color='#fff'>
            <Toolbar>
                <Grid container>

                    <Grid item  >


                    </Grid>

                    <Grid item>
                        <Button color="inherit" style={{marginTop:'15px'}}>Patients</Button>
                        
                        <Button color="inherit" style={{marginTop:'15px'}}>Calender</Button>

                        <Button color="inherit" style={{marginTop:'15px'}}>Users</Button>

                        <Button color="inherit" style={{marginTop:'15px'}}>Billing</Button>
                    </Grid>

                    <Grid item sm>

                    </Grid>

                    <Grid item  >
                        <IconButton>
                            <Badge variant="dot" color="secondary" overlap="circle">
                                <NotificationsIcon style={{fill:"black"}}></NotificationsIcon>
                            </Badge>
                        </IconButton>
                        <IconButton>
                            <Badge>
                                <Avatar alt="Remy Sharp" src="../src/images/1.jpg" />
                            </Badge>
                        </IconButton>
                        

                    </Grid>

                </Grid>
            </Toolbar>

        </AppBar>
    )
}
